00405 ** yyparse - return 0 if worked, 1 if syntax error not recovered from
00406 */
00407 int
00408 yyparse()
00409 {
00410     register YYSTYPE *yypvt;    /* top of value stack for $vars */
00411     unsigned yymaxdepth = YYMAXDEPTH;
00412 
00413     /*
00414     ** Initialize externals - yyparse may be called more than once
00415     */
00416     yyv = (YYSTYPE*)malloc(yymaxdepth*sizeof(YYSTYPE));
00417     yys = (int*)malloc(yymaxdepth*sizeof(int));
00418     if (!yyv || !yys)
00419     {
00420         yyerror( "out of memory" );
00421         return(1);
00422     }
00423     yypv = &yyv[-1];
00424     yyps = &yys[-1];
00425     yystate = 0;
00426     yytmp = 0;
00427     yynerrs = 0;
00428     yyerrflag = 0;
00429     yychar = -1;
00430 
00431     goto yystack;
00432     {
00433         register YYSTYPE *yy_pv;    /* top of value stack */
00434         register int *yy_ps;        /* top of state stack */
00435         register int yy_state;      /* current state */
00436         register int  yy_n;     /* internal state number info */
00437 
00438         /*
00439         ** get globals into registers.
00440         ** branch to here only if YYBACKUP was called.
00441         */
00442     yynewstate:
00443         yy_pv = yypv;
00444         yy_ps = yyps;
00445         yy_state = yystate;
00446         goto yy_newstate;
00447 
00448         /*
00449         ** get globals into registers.
00450         ** either we just started, or we just finished a reduction
00451         */
00452     yystack:
00453         yy_pv = yypv;
00454         yy_ps = yyps;
00455         yy_state = yystate;
00456 
00457         /*
00458         ** top of for (;;) loop while no reductions done
00459         */
00460     yy_stack:
00461         /*
00462         ** put a state and value onto the stacks
00463         */
00464 #if YYDEBUG
00465         /*
00466         ** if debugging, look up token value in list of value vs.
00467         ** name pairs.  0 and negative (-1) are special values.
00468         ** Note: linear search is used since time is not a real
00469         ** consideration while debugging.
00470         */
00471         if ( yydebug )

00473             register int yy_i;
00474 
00475             (void)printf( "State %d, token ", yy_state );
00476             if ( yychar == 0 )
00477                 (void)printf( "end-of-file\n" );
00478             else if ( yychar < 0 )

00482                 for ( yy_i = 0; yytoks[yy_i].t_val >= 0;
00483                     yy_i++ )
00484                 {
00485                     if ( yytoks[yy_i].t_val == yychar )
00486                         break;
00487                 }
00488                 (void)printf( "%s\n", yytoks[yy_i].t_name );

00496             ** have to be reset, or bad things will happen
00497             */
00498             int yyps_index = (yy_ps - yys);
00499             int yypv_index = (yy_pv - yyv);
00500             int yypvt_index = (yypvt - yyv);
00501             yymaxdepth += YYMAXDEPTH;
00502             yyv = (YYSTYPE*)realloc((char*)yyv,
00503                 yymaxdepth * sizeof(YYSTYPE));
00504             yys = (int*)realloc((char*)yys,
00505                 yymaxdepth * sizeof(int));
00506             if (!yyv || !yys)
00507             {
00508                 yyerror( "yacc stack overflow" );
00509                 return(1);
00510             }
00511             yy_ps = yys + yyps_index;
00512             yy_pv = yyv + yypv_index;
00513             yypvt = yyv + yypvt_index;
00514         }
00515         *yy_ps = yy_state;
00516         *++yy_pv = yyval;
00517 
00518         /*
00519         ** we have a new state - find out what to do
00520         */
00521     yy_newstate:
00522         if ( ( yy_n = yypact[ yy_state ] ) <= YYFLAG )
00523             goto yydefault;     /* simple state */
00524 #if YYDEBUG

00526         ** if debugging, need to mark whether new token grabbed
00527         */
00528         yytmp = yychar < 0;
00529 #endif
